'''PCS switching center''': In [[personal communications service]], a facility that (a) supports [[Access network|access]]-independent [[call control]]/service control, and [[Telecommunication connection|connection]] control (switching) functions, and (b) is responsible for [[interconnection]] of access and [[telecommunications network|network]] systems to support end-to-end services.
''Note 1:'' The PCS [[switching center]] represents a collection of one or more [[network element]]s.
''Note 2:'' The term ''"center"'' does not imply a physical location.
==References== {{FS1037C}}
[[Category:Mobile technology]]
{{telecomm-stub}}

