A '''stauroscope''' is an [[optical instrument]] used in determining the position of the planes of light-vibration in sections of [[crystals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://machaut.uchicago.edu/?action=search&resource=Webster%27s&page=1407 |title=Webster's Revised Unabridged Dictionary (1913) - The ARTFL Project |publisher=Machaut.uchicago.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-08-24}}</ref> The word comes from [[Greek language|Greek]] for cross + scope. It was invented by [[Wolfgang Franz von Kobell]] in 1855.
